Alice and Bob both go to a party which starts at 5:00. Each of them arrives at a random time between 5:00 and 6:00. The problem is to find the probability that the total number of minutes Alice and Bob are late for the party is less than 45 minutes. The answer should be expressed as a common fraction.The problem can be visualized using a diagram: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (6,0) -- (6,6) -- (0,6) -- cycle;\draw (0,0) -- (4.5,4.5);
ode at (0,-0.3) {5:00};
ode at (6,-0.3) {6:00};
ode at (-0.3,6) {6:00};
ode at (-0.3,0) {5:00};
ode at (3,-0.6) {Alice's arrival time};
ode at (-0.9,3) {Bob's arrival time};\end{tikzpicture}

In trapezoid $ABCD$, the sides $AB$ and $CD$ are equal. The lengths of the parallel sides are $16$ and $8$, and the height of the trapezoid is $3$, as shown in the diagram below: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (4,3) -- (12,3) -- (16,0) -- cycle;\draw[dashed] (4,0) -- (4,3);\draw (3.5,0) -- (3.5,0.5) -- (4,0.5);
ode[below left] at (0,0) {$A$};
ode[above left] at (4,3) {$B$};
ode[above right] at (12,3) {$C$};
ode[below right] at (16,0) {$D$};
ode[above] at (8,3) {$8$};
ode[below] at (8,0) {$16$};
ode[right] at (4,1.5) {$3$};\end{tikzpicture}What is the perimeter of trapezoid $ABCD$?
